{
  "topicId": "m4-t1",
  "title": "Talking About Money and Asking for Prices in Darija",
  "dialect": "darija",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Introduction to 'Money'",
          "arabic": "مقدمة عن 'المال'"
        },
        "text": "In Moroccan Darija, the most common word for 'money' is 'l-flous'. It's a plural noun, so it's always used in this form. You'll hear this word frequently in everyday transactions.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الفلوس",
            "english": "Money",
            "transliteration": "l-flous"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عندي الفلوس",
            "english": "I have money",
            "transliteration": "3andi l-flous"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "l-flous"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Moroccan Currency: Dirham",
          "arabic": "العملة المغربية: الدرهم"
        },
        "text": "The official currency of Morocco is the Dirham. It's often abbreviated as 'DH' or 'MAD'. When asking or stating prices, you will primarily use 'derham'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "درهم",
            "english": "Dirham",
            "transliteration": "derham"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "عشرين درهم",
            "english": "Twenty Dirhams",
            "transliteration": "3ashrin derham"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "derham"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Small Change: Santim",
          "arabic": "العملة الصغيرة: سنتيم"
        },
        "text": "For smaller denominations, people often use 'santim' (centime). There are 100 santimat in 1 Dirham. Sometimes, people might refer to 'fraṅk' (franc) which also equals 1 santim.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "سنتيم",
            "english": "Centime",
            "transliteration": "santim"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "خمسين سنتيم",
            "english": "Fifty centimes",
            "transliteration": "khamsin santim"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "santim"
      }
    },
    {
