    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How much?'",
          "arabic": "السؤال عن 'بكم؟'"
        },
        "text": "The most common way to ask 'How much?' or 'What's the price?' in Darija is with the word 'shḥal?'. This single word is versatile and can be used on its own.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شحال؟",
            "english": "How much?",
            "transliteration": "shḥal?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "shḥal?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'How much is this?'",
          "arabic": "السؤال عن 'بكم هذا؟'"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'How much is this?' when pointing to an item, you'd combine 'shḥal?' with the demonstrative pronoun 'hada' (this, masculine) or 'hadi' (this, feminine).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شحال هادا؟",
            "english": "How much is this? (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "shḥal hada?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شحال هادي؟",
            "english": "How much is this? (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "shḥal hadi?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "shḥal hada?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking for the price of a specific item",
          "arabic": "السؤال عن سعر سلعة محددة"
        },
        "text": "If you want to ask about a specific item by name, you simply place the item's name after 'shḥal'. For example, 'shḥal l-khubz?' (How much is the bread?).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شحال التفاح؟",
            "english": "How much are the apples?",
            "transliteration": "shḥal t-teffaḥ?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شحال هاد الصاك؟",
            "english": "How much is this bag?",
            "transliteration": "shḥal had ṣ-ṣak?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "shḥal t-teffaḥ?"
      }
    },
