    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Describing something as 'Expensive'",
          "arabic": "وصف شيء بـ 'غالي'"
        },
        "text": "When you think a price is high, you can say 'ghali' for masculine items or 'ghalya' for feminine items. Remember, Darija often makes adjectives agree in gender.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "غالي",
            "english": "Expensive (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "ghali"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "غالية",
            "english": "Expensive (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "ghalya"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هادا غالي.",
            "english": "This is expensive (masc.).",
            "transliteration": "hada ghali."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "ghali, ghalya"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Describing something as 'Cheap'",
          "arabic": "وصف شيء بـ 'رخيص'"
        },
        "text": "If you find something's price low or reasonable, use 'rkhiṣ' for masculine items or 'rkhiṣa' for feminine items.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "رخيص",
            "english": "Cheap (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "rkhiṣ"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "رخيصة",
            "english": "Cheap (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "rkhiṣa"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هادي رخيصة.",
            "english": "This is cheap (fem.).",
            "transliteration": "hadi rkhiṣa."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "rkhiṣ, rkhiṣa"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "'Too Expensive' and Asking for a Discount",
          "arabic": "'غالي بزاف' وطلب تخفيض"
        },
        "text": "To emphasize that something is 'too expensive', add 'bezzerf' (too much/very) after the adjective. You can also directly ask for a discount: 'wach kayn shi takhfiḍ?' (Is there a discount?) or 'nqaṣ shwiya' (Reduce a little).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "غالي بزاف!",
            "english": "Too expensive!",
            "transliteration": "ghali bezzerf!"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "واش كاين شي تخفيض؟",
            "english": "Is there a discount?",
            "transliteration": "wash kayn shi takhfiḍ?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "نقص شوية.",
            "english": "Reduce a little (price).",
            "transliteration": "nqaṣ shwiya."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "ghali bezzerf!"
      }
    },
